Grefsen is a Qt/Wayland compositor providing a minimal desktop environment.

Building:

If you don't have mlite:

cd somewhere/else
git clone https://git.merproject.org/mer-core/mlite.git
cd mlite
qmake
make install

then
cd path/to/grefsen
export PKG_CONFIG_PATH=/home/rutledge/dev/qt5-dbg/qtbase/lib/pkgconfig
(because mlite installs its .pc file there)
qmake
make

Installation:

mkdir ~/.config/grefsen
cp example-config/* ~/.config/grefsen

Then modify to taste.

Running:

You'll need to set the following env variables:

export QT_WAYLAND_DISABLE_WINDOWDECORATION=1
  (avoid Qt drawing its default blue titlebars, so that we can use custom ones)

export QT_AUTO_SCREEN_SCALE_FACTOR=0
  (attempt to avoid hidpi scaling)

cd path/to/grefsen
QML2_IMPORT_PATH=imports ./grefsen

Append "-platform eglfs" to run it on the Linux console.
Otherwise it can run as a window inside an X11 session.

